'''Paleomycology''' is the study of [[fossil]] [[fungi]].<ref>{{cite journal |author=Brown OLM |year= 2004|title=Fossil fungi or paleomycology |journal=Interciencia |volume=29 |issue=2 |pages=94–98 |language=Spanish }}</ref> A paleomycologist is someone who works in this field. Paleomycology is considered a subdiscipline of [[paleobotany]].<ref>{{cite book |author1=Taylor, Thomas N. |author2=Taylor, Edith L. |author3=Krings, Michael |title=Paleobotany: The Biology and Evolution of Fossil Plants, Second Edition |publisher=Academic Press |location=Boston |year=2009 |page=98 |isbn=0-12-373972-1 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_29tNNeQKeMC&lpg=PA98&dq=Paleomycology&lr=&pg=PA98#v=onepage&q=Paleomycology&f=false |accessdate=2010-01-15}}</ref>
